<div id="banner">
	<h1>Tokelau Gives Free Domains</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Tokelau, a small island in the Pacific is inhabited by less than 1500 people. They&#8217;ve always divided their share of fish among the people equally and so now that they&#8217;ve got their own top-level domain (.tk) <a href="http://dot.tk/vc00500.html">they&#8217;re giving those away for free too</a>.</p>

<p>This is an awesome departure from VeriSign&#8217;s $70 fleecing. Congrats to the .tk maintainers for having the courage to do this! Unfortunately, free domains only support web page redirections (and seem to require pop-up ads for dot.tk) but registering a domain is only $10 a year.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 12, 2002 02:04 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000499" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

